channel.title: Doesn't load
channel.description:
Okay, I haven't coded since 2012 pretty much. Way before this crappy EOC thing happened. I still stay with 317 loading 508. But with a 2 year gap where I haven't coded or played I sorta forgot a lot of stuff. I downloaded InsidiaXV8 and started it up but I can't log on. There is an error but I believe it is only for mapConfig or something and I am not to sure that is important.
Anyway, below is a picture that will explain my problem. I hope it helps.

I am still having trouble logging in though so I guess I need to look that up some more.

item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

[quote=“Pure_, post:5, topic:542023”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=660897.msg4418277#msg4418277 date=1397068580]
I believe this error is because there’s a Thumbs.db file somewhere in your cache (can’t remember where) and for some reason it makes the mapConfig.txt look not there.
You might have to turn on hidden files/folders in the control panel of your computer to see it.
[/quote]I doubt that would make a difference… See this.[/quote]
I just remember hearing that someone fixed it that way.
OP: Check to make sure the filepath in the picture is valid, and the contents of the mapConfig.txt are correct. You can find out if they are in the setNewMaps method (I think).
